[2
Date: 19 May 2001
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: GIDEON database

There are approximately 10 dogs for every human in the Philippines.
275 cases of human rabies were reported in 1978. 479 cases were reported
in 1994 - 37.8% were below age 15, and most cases were acquired from dogs.
230 cases were reported in 1995; 337 in 1996 (all from dogs); 325 in 1997
(all from dogs); 362 in 1998 (all from dogs); 398 in 1999.
27 502 postexposure treatment courses were administered in 1988; 3680 in
1994; 11 338 in 1996; 39 015 in 1997; 42 760 in 1998.
828 rabid animals were reported in 1993 (including 825 dogs); 1040 in 1994)
1039 dogs and 1 cat); 767 in 1996 (749 dogs); 1966 in 1997 (1957 dogs, 8
cats, 1 ruminant); 1828 in 1998.
